#: serverguide/C/security.xml:897(para)
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"http://www.netfilter.org/documentation/HOWTO/NAT-"
"HOWTO.html\">nat-HOWTO</ulink> contains further details on masquerading."
msgstr ""
"Le <ulink url=\"http://www.linux-france.org/prj/inetdoc/guides/NAT-"
"HOWTO/\">guide pratique du NAT</ulink> contient plus de renseignements sur "
"le masquage IP."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:903(para)
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/IptablesHowTo\">IPTables "
"HowTo</ulink> in the Ubuntu wiki is a great resource."
msgstr ""
"La page du Wiki Ubuntu (en anglais) <ulink "
"url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/IptablesHowTo\">IPTables "
"HowTo</ulink> est également une très bonne source d'informations."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:911(title)
msgid "AppArmor"
msgstr "AppArmor"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:912(para)
msgid ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> is a Linux Security Module "
"implementation of name-based mandatory access controls. AppArmor confines "
"individual programs to a set of listed files and posix 1003.1e draft "
"capabilities."
msgstr ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> est une implémentation de contrôles "
"d'accès obligatoires basée sur l'infrastructure LSM (Linux Security Module). "
"AppArmor restreint les programmes individuels à un ensemble de fichiers "
"répertoriés et de capacités définies dans l'ébauche POSIX 1003.1e."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:916(para)
msgid ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> is installed and loaded by default. It "
"uses <emphasis>profiles</emphasis> of an application to determine what files "
"and permissions the application requires. Some packages will install their "
"own profiles, and additional profiles can be found in the "
"<application>apparmor-profiles</application> package."
msgstr ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> est installé et chargé en mémoire par "
"défault. Il utilise des <emphasis>profils</emphasis> d'application afin de "
"déterminer quels fichiers et quelles permissions l'application nécessite. "
"Certains paquets installent leurs propres profils, et des profils "
"additionnels se trouvent dans le paquet <application>apparmor-"
"profiles</application>."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:921(para)
msgid ""
"To install the <application>apparmor-profiles</application> package from a "
"terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Pour installer le paquet <application>apparmor-profiles</application> depuis "
"un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:927(para)
msgid "AppArmor profiles have two modes of execution:"
msgstr "Les profils d'AppArmor ont deux modes d'exécution :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:932(para)
msgid ""
"Complaining/Learning: profile violations are permitted and logged. Useful "
"for testing and developing new profiles."
msgstr ""
"Réclamation/apprentissage : les infractions au profil sont autorisées et "
"journalisées. C'est utile pour tester et développer de nouveaux profils."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:937(para)
msgid ""
"Enforced/Confined: enforces profile policy as well as logging the violation."
msgstr ""
"Imposé/restreint : la politique du profil est imposée et les infractions "
"sont journalisées."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:943(title)
msgid "Using AppArmor"
msgstr "Utilisation d'AppArmor"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:944(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>apparmor-utils</application> package contains command line "
"utilities that you can use to change the <application>AppArmor</application> "
"execution mode, find the status of a profile, create new profiles, etc."
msgstr ""
"Le paquet <application>apparmor-utils</application> contient des utilitaires "
"en ligne de commande que vous pouvez utiliser pour changer le mode "
"d'exécution d'<application>AppArmor</application>, trouver l'état d'un "
"profil, créer de nouveaux profils, etc."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:950(para)
msgid ""
"<application>apparmor_status</application> is used to view the current "
"status of AppArmor profiles."
msgstr ""
"<application>apparmor_status</application> est utilisé pour voir l'état "
"actuel des profils d'AppArmor."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:954(command)
msgid "sudo apparmor_status"
msgstr "sudo apparmor_status"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:958(para)
msgid ""
"<application>aa-complain</application> places a profile into "
"<emphasis>complain</emphasis> mode."
msgstr ""
"<application>aa-complain</application> place un profil en mode "
"<emphasis>complain</emphasis> (réclamation)."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:962(command)
msgid "sudo aa-complain /path/to/bin"
msgstr "sudo aa-complain /chemin/vers/application"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:966(para)
msgid ""
"<application>aa-enforce</application> places a profile into "
"<emphasis>enforce</emphasis> mode."
msgstr ""
"<application>aa-enforce</application> place un profil en mode "
"<emphasis>enforce</emphasis> (imposé)."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:970(command)
msgid "sudo aa-enforce /path/to/bin"
msgstr "sudo aa-enforce /chemin/vers/application"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:974(para)
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/apparmor.d</filename> directory is where the AppArmor "
"profiles are located. It can be used to manipulate the "
"<emphasis>mode</emphasis> of all profiles."
msgstr ""
"Le répertoire <filename>/etc/apparmor.d</filename> est l'endroit où se "
"situent les profils d'AppArmor. Il peut être utilisé pour manipuler le "
"<emphasis>mode</emphasis> de l'ensemble des profils."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:978(para)
msgid "Enter the following to place all profiles into complain mode:"
msgstr ""
"Saisissez ce qui suit pour placer tous les profils en mode complain "
"(recommandation) :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:982(command)
msgid "sudo aa-complain /etc/apparmor.d/*"
msgstr "sudo aa-complain /etc/apparmor.d/*"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:984(para)
msgid "To place all profiles in enforce mode:"
msgstr "Pour placer tous les profils en mode enforce (imposé) :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:988(command)
msgid "sudo aa-enforce /etc/apparmor.d/*"
msgstr "sudo aa-enforce /etc/apparmor.d/*"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:992(para)
msgid ""
"<application>apparmor_parser</application> is used to load a profile into "
"the kernel. It can also be used to reload a currently loaded profile using "
"the <emphasis>-r</emphasis> option. To load a profile:"
msgstr ""
"<application>apparmor_parser</application> est utilisé pour charger un "
"profil dans le noyau. Il peut aussi être utilisé pour recharger un profil "
"déjà chargé en utilisant l'option <emphasis>-r</emphasis>. Pour charger un "
"profil :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:997(command) serverguide/C/security.xml:1029(command)
msgid "cat /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name | sudo apparmor_parser -a"
msgstr "cat /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name | sudo apparmor_parser -a"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:999(para)
msgid "To reload a profile:"
msgstr "Pour recharger un profil :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1003(command)
msgid "cat /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name | sudo apparmor_parser -r"
msgstr "cat /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name | sudo apparmor_parser -r"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1007(para)
msgid ""
"<filename>/etc/init.d/apparmor</filename> can be used to "
"<emphasis>reload</emphasis> all profiles:"
msgstr ""
"<filename>/etc/init.d/apparmor</filename> peut être utilisé pour "
"<emphasis>recharger</emphasis> tous les profils :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1011(command) serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:632(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/apparmor reload"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/apparmor reload"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1015(para)
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/disable</filename> directory can be used along "
"with the <application>apparmor_parser -R</application> option to "
"<emphasis>disable</emphasis> a profile."
msgstr ""
"Le répertoire <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/disable</filename> peut être utilisé "
"en même temps que l'option <application>apparmor_parser -R</application> "
"pour <emphasis>désactiver</emphasis> un profil."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1020(command)
msgid "sudo ln -s /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name /etc/apparmor.d/disable/"
msgstr "sudo ln -s /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name /etc/apparmor.d/disable/"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1021(command)
msgid "sudo apparmor_parser -R /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name"
msgstr "sudo apparmor_parser -R /etc/apparmor.d/profile.name"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1023(para)
msgid ""
"To <emphasis>re-enable</emphasis> a disabled profile remove the symbolic "
"link to the profile in <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/disable/</filename>. Then "
"load the profile using the <emphasis>-a</emphasis> option."
msgstr ""
"Afin de <emphasis>ré-activer</emphasis> un profil désactivé, supprimez le "
"lien symbolique vers le profil dans "
"<filename>/etc/apparmor.d/disable/</filename>. Puis chargez le profil en "
"utilisant l'option <emphasis>-a</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1028(command)
msgid "sudo rm /etc/apparmor.d/disable/profile.name"
msgstr "sudo rm /etc/apparmor.d/disable/profile.name"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1033(para)
msgid ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> can be disabled, and the kernel module "
"unloaded by entering the following:"
msgstr ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> peut être désactivé, et le module "
"déchargé du noyau en entrant les lignes suivantes :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1037(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/apparmor stop"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/apparmor stop"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1038(command)
msgid "sudo update-rc.d -f apparmor remove"
msgstr "sudo update-rc.d -f apparmor remove"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1042(para)
msgid "To re-enable <application>AppArmor</application> enter:"
msgstr "Pour réactiver <application>AppArmor</application> saisissez :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1046(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/apparmor start"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/apparmor start"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1047(command)
msgid "sudo update-rc.d apparmor defaults"
msgstr "sudo update-rc.d apparmor defaults"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1052(para)
msgid ""
"Replace <emphasis>profile.name</emphasis> with the name of the profile you "
"want to manipulate. Also, replace <filename>/path/to/bin/</filename> with "
"the actual executable file path. For example for the "
"<application>ping</application> command use <filename>/bin/ping</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Remplacez <emphasis>nom.profil</emphasis> avec le nom du profil que vous "
"souhaitez manipuler. Remplacez aussi "
"<filename>/chemin/vers/application</filename> avec le chemin d'accès de "
"l'exécutable en cours. Par exemple, pour la commande "
"<application>ping</application> utilisez <filename>/bin/ping</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1060(title)
msgid "Profiles"
msgstr "Profils"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1061(para)
msgid ""
"<application>AppArmor</application> profiles are simple text files located "
"in <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/</filename>. The files are named after the full "
"path to the executable they profile replacing the \"/\" with \".\". For "
"example <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/bin.ping</filename> is the AppArmor "
"profile for the <filename>/bin/ping</filename> command."
msgstr ""
"Les profils <application>AppArmor</application> sont de simples fichiers "
"texte qui se trouvent dans <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/</filename>. Les "
"fichiers portent le nom du chemin d'accès entier de l'exécutable dont ils "
"sont les profils en remplaçant \"/\" par \".\". Par exemple "
"<filename>/etc/apparmor.d/bin.ping</filename> est le profil AppArmor de la "
"commande <filename>/bin/ping</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1067(para)
msgid "There are two main type of rules used in profiles:"
msgstr "Il existe deux grands types de règles utilisées dans les profils :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1072(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Path entries:</emphasis> which detail which files an application "
"can access in the file system."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Path entries :</emphasis> les fichiers auxquels une une "
"application peut avoir accès dans le système de fichier."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1077(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Capability entries:</emphasis> determine what privileges a "
"confined process is allowed to use."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Capability entries :</emphasis> détermine les privilèges qu'un "
"processus restreint est autoriser à utiliser."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1082(para)
msgid ""
"As an example take a look at <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/bin.ping</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"A titre d'exemple, jetez un œil à "
"<filename>/etc/apparmor.d/bin.ping</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1085(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"#include &lt;tunables/global&gt;\n"
"/bin/ping flags=(complain) {\n"
"  #include &lt;abstractions/base&gt;\n"
"  #include &lt;abstractions/consoles&gt;\n"
"  #include &lt;abstractions/nameservice&gt;\n"
"\n"
"  capability net_raw,\n"
"  capability setuid,\n"
"  network inet raw,\n"
"  \n"
"  /bin/ping mixr,\n"
"  /etc/modules.conf r,\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"#include &lt;tunables/global&gt;\n"
"/bin/ping flags=(complain) {\n"
"#include &lt;abstractions/base&gt;\n"
"#include &lt;abstractions/consoles&gt;\n"
"#include &lt;abstractions/nameservice&gt;\n"
"\n"
"capability net_raw,\n"
"capability setuid,\n"
"network inet raw,\n"
"\n"
"/bin/ping mixr,\n"
"/etc/modules.conf r,\n"
"}\n"

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1102(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>#include &lt;tunables/global&gt;:</emphasis> include statements "
"from other files. This allows statements pertaining to multiple applications "
"to be placed in a common file."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>#include &lt;tunables/global&gt;:</emphasis> directives "
"d'inclusion d'autres fichiers. Ceci permet de placer dans un fichier commun "
"les directives dépendant de plusieurs applications."

#: serverguide/C/security.xml:1108(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>/bin/ping flags=(complain):</emphasis> path to the profiled "
"program, also setting the mode to <emphasis>complain</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>/bin/ping flags=(complain):</emphasis> chemin de l'exécutable et "
"réglage du mode sur <emphasis>complain</emphasis> (réclamation)."

