msgstr ""
"Le chemin <emphasis>smtpd_sasl_path</emphasis> est un chemin relatif au "
"répertoire de la file d'attente (queue) de Postfix."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:137(para)
msgid ""
"Next, obtain a digital certificate for TLS. See <xref linkend=\"certificates-"
"and-security\"/> for details. This example also uses a Certificate Authority "
"(CA). For information on generating a CA certificate see <xref "
"linkend=\"certificate-authority\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:143(para)
msgid ""
"You can get the digital certificate from a certificate authority. But unlike "
"web clients, SMTP clients rarely complain about \"self-signed "
"certificates\", so alternatively, you can create the certificate yourself. "
"Refer to <xref linkend=\"creating-a-self-signed-certificate\"/> for more "
"details."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez obtenir le certificat numérique d'une autorité de certification. "
"Cependant, à la différence des clients Web, les clients SMTP envoient "
"rarement un avertissement  pour les « certificats auto-signés », vous pouvez "
"donc créer le certificat vous-même. Voir <xref linkend=\"creating-a-self-"
"signed-certificate\"/> pour plus de renseignements"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:155(para)
msgid ""
"Once you have a certificate, configure Postfix to provide TLS encryption for "
"both incoming and outgoing mail:"
msgstr ""
"Une fois que vous avez un certificat, configurez Postfix pour fournir "
"l'encryptage à l'aide du protocole TLS des e-mails entrants et sortants :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:158(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_auth_only = no'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtp_use_tls = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_use_tls = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtp_tls_note_starttls_offer = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_key_file = /etc/ssl/private/server.key'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_cert_file = /etc/ssl/certs/server.crt'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_loglevel = 1'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_received_header = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_session_cache_timeout = 3600s'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'tls_random_source = dev:/dev/urandom'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'myhostname = mail.example.com'\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_auth_only = no'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtp_use_tls = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_use_tls = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtp_tls_note_starttls_offer = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_key_file = /etc/ssl/private/server.key'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_cert_file = /etc/ssl/certs/server.crt'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_loglevel = 1'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_received_header = yes'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_session_cache_timeout = 3600s'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'tls_random_source = dev:/dev/urandom'\n"
"sudo postconf -e 'myhostname = mail.example.com'\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:173(para)
msgid ""
"If you are using your own <emphasis>Certificate Authority</emphasis> to sign "
"the certificate enter:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:177(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_CAfile = /etc/ssl/certs/cacert.pem'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_CAfile = /etc/ssl/certs/cacert.pem'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:180(para)
msgid ""
"Again, for more details about certificates see <xref linkend=\"certificates-"
"and-security\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:186(para)
msgid ""
"After running all the commands, <application>Postfix</application> is "
"configured for SMTP-AUTH and a self-signed certificate has been created for "
"TLS encryption."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir exécuté toutes les commandes, <application>Postfix</application> "
"est configuré pour SMTP-AUTH et un certificat autosigné a été créé pour le "
"cryptage TLS."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:191(para)
msgid ""
"Now, the file <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename> should look like "
"<ulink url=\"../sample/postfix_configuration\">this</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, le fichier <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename> doit "
"ressembler à <ulink url=\"../sample/postfix_configuration\">ceci</ulink>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:195(para)
msgid ""
"The postfix initial configuration is complete. Run the following command to "
"restart the postfix daemon:"
msgstr ""
"La configuration initiale de Postfix est terminée. Tapez la commande "
"suivante pour redémarrer le démon Postfix :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:201(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:315(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:378(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:984(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:1561(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/postfix restart"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/postfix restart"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:204(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Postfix</application> supports SMTP-AUTH as defined in <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.isi.edu/in-notes/rfc2554.txt\">RFC2554</ulink>. It is based "
"on <ulink url=\"ftp://ftp.isi.edu/in-notes/rfc2222.txt\">SASL</ulink>. "
"However it is still necessary to set up SASL authentication before you can "
"use SMTP-AUTH."
msgstr ""
"<application>Postfix</application> prend en charge SMTP-AUTH comme défini "
"dans la <ulink url=\"ftp://ftp.isi.edu/in-"
"notes/rfc2554.txt\">RFC2554</ulink>. Ceci est basé sur <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.isi.edu/in-notes/rfc2222.txt\">SASL</ulink>. Cependant, il "
"reste nécessaire de configurer l'authentification SASL avant de pouvoir "
"utiliser SMTP-AUTH."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:214(title) serverguide/C/mail.xml:609(title)
msgid "Configuring SASL"
msgstr "Configuration de SASL"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:215(para)
msgid ""
"Postfix supports two SASL implementations Cyrus SASL and Dovecot SASL. To "
"enable Dovecot SASL the <application>dovecot-common</application> package "
"will need to be installed. From a terminal prompt enter the following:"
msgstr ""
"Postfix prend en charge deux implémentations SASL : Cyrus SASL et Dovecot "
"SASL. Afin d'activer l'implémentation Dovecot SASL, le paquet "
"<application>dovecot-common</application> aura besoin d'être installé. Dans "
"un terminal, saisissez :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:221(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install dovecot-common"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install dovecot-common"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:223(para)
msgid ""
"Next you will need to edit <filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>. "
"In the <emphasis>auth default</emphasis> section uncomment the "
"<emphasis>socket listen</emphasis> option and change the following:"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant vous allez devoir éditer "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>. Dans la section "
"<emphasis>auth default</emphasis> annulez le commentaire de l'option "
"<emphasis>socket listen</emphasis> et modifiez ce qui suit:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:227(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"  socket listen {\n"
"    #master {\n"
"      # Master socket provides access to userdb information. It's typically\n"
"      # used to give Dovecot's local delivery agent access to userdb so it\n"
"      # can find mailbox locations.\n"
"      #path = /var/run/dovecot/auth-master\n"
"      #mode = 0600\n"
"      # Default user/group is the one who started dovecot-auth (root)\n"
"      #user = \n"
"      #group = \n"
"    #}\n"
"    client {\n"
"      # The client socket is generally safe to export to everyone. Typical "
"use\n"
"      # is to export it to your SMTP server so it can do SMTP AUTH lookups\n"
"      # using it.\n"
"      path = /var/spool/postfix/private/auth-client\n"
"      mode = 0660\n"
"      user = postfix\n"
"      group = postfix\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"  socket listen {\n"
"    #master {\n"
"      # Master socket provides access to userdb information. It's typically\n"
"      # used to give Dovecot's local delivery agent access to userdb so it\n"
"      # can find mailbox locations.\n"
"      #path = /var/run/dovecot/auth-master\n"
"      #mode = 0600\n"
"      # Default user/group is the one who started dovecot-auth (root)\n"
"      #user = \n"
"      #group = \n"
"    #}\n"
"    client {\n"
"      # The client socket is generally safe to export to everyone. Typical "
"use\n"
"      # is to export it to your SMTP server so it can do SMTP AUTH lookups\n"
"      # using it.\n"
"      path = /var/spool/postfix/private/auth-client\n"
"      mode = 0660\n"
"      user = postfix\n"
"      group = postfix\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:251(para)
msgid ""
"In order to let <application>Outlook</application> clients use SMTPAUTH, in "
"the <emphasis>auth default</emphasis> section of /etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf "
"add <emphasis>\"login\"</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""
"Dans le but de permettre aux clients <application>Outlook</application> "
"d'utiliser SMTPAUTH, ajoutez dans la section <emphasis>auth "
"default</emphasis>du fichier /etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf : "
"<emphasis>\"login\"</emphasis>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:256(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"  mechanisms = plain login\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"  mechanisms = plain login\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:260(para)
msgid ""
"Once you have <application>Dovecot</application> configured restart it with:"
msgstr ""
"Une fois que vous avez configuré <application>Dovecot</application>, faites "
"le redémarrer avec :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:264(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:735(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/dovecot restart"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/dovecot restart"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:269(title)
msgid "Postfix-Dovecot"
msgstr "Postfix-Dovecot"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:271(para)
msgid ""
"Another option for configuring <application>Postfix</application> for SMTP-"
"AUTH is using the <application>dovecot-postfix</application> package. This "
"package will install <application>Dovecot</application> and configure "
"<application>Postfix</application> to use it for both SASL authentication "
"and as a Mail Delivery Agent (MDA). The package also configures "
"<application>Dovecot</application> for IMAP, IMAPS, POP3, and POP3S."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:280(para)
msgid ""
"You may or may not want to run IMAP, IMAPS, POP3, or POP3S on your mail "
"server. For example, if you are configuring your server to be a mail "
"gateway, spam/virus filter, etc. If this is the case it may be easier to use "
"the above commands to configure Postfix for SMTPAUTH."
msgstr ""
"C'est vous de choisir si vous voulez utiliser IMAP, IMAPS, POP3, ou POP3S "
"sur votre serveur de mail. Par exemple, si vous configurez votre serveur "
"pour être une passerelle mail, un filtre spam/virus, etc. Si c'est le cas, "
"il serait plus simple d'utiliser les commandes ci-dessus pour configurer "
"Postfix pour SMTPAUTH."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:287(para)
msgid "To install the package, from a terminal prompt enter:"
msgstr "Pour installer le paquet, saisissez dans un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:292(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install dovecot-postfix"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install dovecot-postfix"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:295(para)
msgid ""
"You should now have a working mail server, but there are a few options that "
"you may wish to further customize. For example, the package uses the "
"certificate and key from the <application>ssl-cert</application> package, "
"and in a production environment you should use a certificate and key "
"generated for the host. See <xref linkend=\"certificates-and-security\"/> "
"for more details."
msgstr ""
"Votre serveur de courriel devrait être opérationnel, mais vous voudrez sans "
"doute configurer certaines options. Par exemple, le paquet utilise le "
"certificat et la clé du paquet <application>ssl-cert</application>, mais "
"dans un environnement de production, vous devriez utiliser un certificat et "
"une clef créée pour l'hôte. Consultez <xref linkend=\"certificates-and-"
"security\"/> pour de plus amples informations."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:301(para)
msgid ""
"Once you have a customized certificate and key for the host, change the "
"following options in <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Changez les options suivantes dans <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename> "
"une fois que vous avez personnalisé un certificat et une clé pour l'hôte :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:305(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtpd_tls_cert_file = /etc/ssl/certs/ssl-mail.pem\n"
"smtpd_tls_key_file = /etc/ssl/private/ssl-mail.key\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtpd_tls_cert_file = /etc/ssl/certs/ssl-mail.pem\n"
"smtpd_tls_key_file = /etc/ssl/private/ssl-mail.key\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:310(para)
msgid "Then restart Postfix:"
msgstr "Redémarrez ensuite Postfix :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:321(para)
msgid ""
"SMTP-AUTH configuration is complete. Now it is time to test the setup."
msgstr ""
"La configuration de SMTP-AUTH est terminée. Il est maintenant temps de "
"tester la configuration."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:324(para)
msgid "To see if SMTP-AUTH and TLS work properly, run the following command:"
msgstr ""
"Pour vérifier que SMTP-AUTH et TLS fonctionnent correctement, exécutez la "
"commande suivante :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:329(command)
msgid "telnet mail.example.com 25"
msgstr "telnet mail.example.com 25"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:331(para)
msgid ""
"After you have established the connection to the postfix mail server, type:"
msgstr "Après avoir établi la connexion au serveur Postfix, tapez :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:335(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"ehlo mail.example.com\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"ehlo mail.example.com\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:338(para)
msgid ""
"If you see the following lines among others, then everything is working "
"perfectly. Type <command>quit</command> to exit."
msgstr ""
"Si vous voyez, entre autres, les lignes suivantes, alors tout fonctionne "
"parfaitement. Tapez <command>quit</command> pour sortir."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:342(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"250-STARTTLS\n"
"250-AUTH LOGIN PLAIN\n"
"250-AUTH=LOGIN PLAIN\n"
"250 8BITMIME\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"250-STARTTLS\n"
"250-AUTH LOGIN PLAIN\n"
"250-AUTH=LOGIN PLAIN\n"
"250 8BITMIME\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:352(para)
msgid ""
"This section introduces some common ways to determine the cause if problems "
"arise."
msgstr ""
"Cette section introduit les méthodes de base pour déterminer les causes d'un "
"éventuel problème."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:356(title)
msgid "Escaping chroot"
msgstr "Échappement du chroot"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:357(para)
msgid ""
"The Ubuntu <application>postfix</application> package will by default "
"install into a <emphasis>chroot</emphasis> environment for security reasons. "
"This can add greater complexity when troubleshooting problems."
msgstr ""
"Le paquet <application>postfix</application> d'Ubuntu s'installera par "
"défaut dans un environnement <emphasis>chroot</emphasis> par mesure de "
"sécurité. Ceci peut accroître la complexité de la résolution de problèmes."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:361(para)
msgid ""
"To turn off the chroot operation locate for the following line in the "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> configuration file:"
msgstr ""
"Pour désactiver l'opération chroot essayez de trouver la ligne suivante dans "
"le fichier de configuration <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:365(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp      inet  n       -       -       -       -       smtpd\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp inet n - - - - smtpd\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:368(para)
msgid "and modify it as follows:"
msgstr "et la modifier ainsi :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:371(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp      inet  n       -       n       -       -       smtpd\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp inet n - n - - smtpd\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:374(para)
msgid ""
"You will then need to restart Postfix to use the new configuration. From a "
"terminal prompt enter:"
msgstr ""
"Vous devrez ensuite redémarrer Postfix pour utiliser la nouvelle "
"configuration. A parti d'un terminal, saisissez :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:382(title)
msgid "Log Files"
msgstr "Fichiers journaux"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:383(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Postfix</application> sends all log messages to "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.log</filename>. However error and warning messages "
"can sometimes get lost in the normal log output so they are also logged to "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.err</filename> and "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.warn</filename> respectively."
msgstr ""
"<application>Postfix</application> inscrit tous les messages de "
"journalisation dans <filename>/var/log/mail.log</filename>. Cependant, les "
"erreurs et les alertes peuvent quelquefois disparaître dans les messages "
"normaux, ils sont donc également inscrits dans "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.err</filename> et "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.warn</filename> respectivement."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:388(para)
msgid ""
"To see messages entered into the logs in real time you can use the "
"<application>tail -f</application> command:"
msgstr ""
"Pour voir en temps réel les messages inscrits dans les journaux, vous pouvez "
"utiliser la commande <application>tail -f</application> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:393(command)
msgid "tail -f /var/log/mail.err"
msgstr "tail -f /var/log/mail.err"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:395(para)
msgid ""
"The amount of detail that is recorded in the logs can be increased. Below "
"are some configuration options for increasing the log level for some of the "
"areas covered above."
msgstr ""
"La quantité de renseignements enregistrés dans les journaux peut être "
"augmenté. Voici quelques options de configuration afin d'augmenter le niveau "
"de journalisation pour certains des domaines visés ci-dessus."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:401(para)
msgid ""
"To increase <emphasis>TLS</emphasis> activity logging set the "
"<emphasis>smtpd_tls_loglevel</emphasis> option to a value from 1 to 4."
msgstr ""
"Afin d'accroître l'activité de log de <emphasis>TLS</emphasis>, configurez "
"l'option <emphasis>smtpd_tls_loglevel</emphasis> sur une valeur entre 1 et 4."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:405(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_loglevel = 4'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_loglevel = 4'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:409(para)
msgid ""
"If you are having trouble sending or receiving mail from a specific domain "
"you can add the domain to the <emphasis>debug_peer_list</emphasis> parameter."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez des problèmes d'envoi ou de réception de courriers "
"électroniques en provenance d'un domaine spécifique vous pouvez ajouter ce "
"domaine à la directive <emphasis>debug_peer_list</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:414(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'debug_peer_list = problem.domain'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'debug_peer_list = problem.domain'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:418(para)
msgid ""
"You can increase the verbosity of any <application>Postfix</application> "
"daemon process by editing the <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> "
"and adding a <emphasis>-v</emphasis> after the entry. For example edit the "
"<emphasis>smtp</emphasis> entry:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez accroître la verbosité de n'importe quel démon "
"<application>Postfix</application> en modifiant "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> et en ajoutant <emphasis>-"
"v</emphasis> après l'entrée. Par exemple, modifiez l'entrée "
"<emphasis>smtp</emphasis> :"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:422(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp      unix  -       -       -       -       -       smtp -v\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp unix - - - - - smtp -v\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:428(para)
msgid ""
"It is important to note that after making one of the logging changes above "
"the <application>Postfix</application> process will need to be reloaded in "
"order to recognize the new configuration: <command>sudo /etc/init.d/postfix "
"reload</command>"
msgstr ""
"Il est important de noter qu'après avoir effectué l'une des modifications de "
"log ci-dessus, le processus <application>Postfix</application> devra être "
"rechargé afin de reconnaître la nouvelle configuration : <command>sudo "
"/etc/init.d/postfix reload</command>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:435(para)
msgid ""
"To increase the amount of information logged when troubleshooting "
"<emphasis>SASL</emphasis> issues you can set the following options in "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Afin d'accroitre la quantité d'informations inscrites dans le log lors de la "
"résolution de problèmes avec <emphasis>SASL</emphasis>, vous pouvez "
"configurer les options suivantes dans "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:439(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"auth_debug=yes\n"
"auth_debug_passwords=yes\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"auth_debug=yes\n"
"auth_debug_passwords=yes\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:446(para)
msgid ""
"Just like <application>Postfix</application> if you change a "
"<application>Dovecot</application> configuration the process will need to be "
"reloaded: <command>sudo /etc/init.d/dovecot reload</command>."
msgstr ""
"Comme avec <application>Postfix</application>, si vous changez la "
"configuration de <application>Dovecot</application>, vous devrez le "
"redémarrer afin de prendre en compte ces changements: <command>sudo "
"/etc/init.d/dovecot reload</command>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:452(para)
msgid ""
"Some of the options above can drastically increase the amount of information "
"sent to the log files. Remember to return the log level back to normal after "
"you have corrected the problem. Then reload the appropriate daemon for the "
"new configuration to take affect."
msgstr ""
"Certaines options ci-dessous peuvent dramatiquement augmenter la quantité "
"d'informations inscrites dans les fichiers journaux. Pensez à ramener le "
"niveau de journalisation à la normale une fois que vous aurez détecté et "
"corrigé le problème. Ensuite redémarrez le démon afin que la nouvelle "
"configuration soit prise en compte."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:460(para)
msgid ""
"Administering a <application>Postfix</application> server can be a very "
"complicated task. At some point you may need to turn to the Ubuntu community "
"for more experienced help."
msgstr ""
"Administrer un serveur <application>Postfix</application> peut être une "
"tâche très complexe. À un certain moment, vous devrez peut-être vous tourner "
"vers la communauté Ubuntu pour être aidé par des utilisateurs plus "
"expérimentés."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:464(para)
msgid ""
"A great place to ask for <application>Postfix</application> assistance, and "
"get involved with the Ubuntu Server community, is the <emphasis>#ubuntu-"
"server</emphasis> IRC channel on <ulink "
"url=\"http://freenode.net\">freenode</ulink>. You can also post a message to "
"one of the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support/community/webforums\">Web Forums</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Un endroit génial pour demander de l'assistance pour "
"<application>Postfix</application> et s'impliquer dans la communauté Ubuntu "
"Server, est le canal IRC (anglophone) <emphasis>#ubuntu-server</emphasis> "
"sur <ulink url=\"http://freenode.net\">freenode</ulink>. Vous pouvez aussi "
"poster un message sur les <ulink url=\"http://forum.ubuntu-fr.org/\">forums "
"Ubuntu francophones</ulink>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:469(para)
msgid ""
"For in depth <application>Postfix</application> information Ubuntu "
"developers highly recommend: <ulink url=\"http://www.postfix-book.com/\">The "
"Book of Postfix</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Pour des informations plus complètes sur <application>Postfix</application>, "
"les développeurs Ubuntu recommandent vivement :<ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postfix-book.com/\">The Book of Postfix</ulink>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:473(para)
msgid ""
"Finally, the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postfix.org/documentation.html\">Postfix</ulink> website "
"also has great documentation on all the different configuration options "
"available."
msgstr ""
"Enfin, le site web <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postfix.org/documentation.html\">Postfix</ulink> possède "
"également une grande documentation sur toutes les différentes options de "
"configuration disponibles."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:477(para)
msgid ""
"Also, the <ulink url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Postfix\">Ubuntu "
