#: serverguide/C/introduction.xml:55(para)
msgid ""
"There are a couple of different ways that Ubuntu Server Edition is "
"supported, commercial support and community support. The main commercial "
"support (and development funding) is available from Canonical Ltd. They "
"supply reasonably priced support contracts on a per desktop or per server "
"basis. For more information see the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.canonical.com/services/support\">Canonical Services</ulink> "
"page."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/introduction.xml:62(para)
msgid ""
"Community support is also provided by dedicated individuals, and companies, "
"that wish to make Ubuntu the best distribution possible. Support is provided "
"through multiple mailing lists, IRC channels, forums, blogs, wikis, etc. The "
"large amount of information available can be overwhelming, but a good search "
"engine query can usually provide an answer to your questions. See the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support\">Ubuntu Support</ulink> page for more "
"information."
msgstr ""
"L'assistance communautaire est dispensée par des particuliers dévoués et des "
"sociétés qui ont le désir de faire d'Ubuntu la meilleure des distributions. "
"L'assistance est accessible au travers de multiples listes de diffusion, de "
"canaux IRC, de forums, blogs, wikis, etc. La quantité impressionnante "
"d'informations disponible peut être écrasante mais une requête bien "
"construite dans un moteur de recherche donnera généralement une réponse à "
"vos questions. Voir <ulink url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support\">Ubuntu "
"Support</ulink> pour de plus amples informations."

