#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:54(para)
msgid ""
"The Server Edition provides a common base for all sorts of server "
"applications. It is a minimalist design providing a platform for the desired "
"services, such as file/print services, web hosting, email hosting, etc."
msgstr ""
"L'édition serveur fournit une base commune à toutes sortes de programmes "
"serveurs. Sa conception minimaliste offre une plate-forme pour de multiples "
"services, tels que serveur de fichier ou d'impression, hébergement Web, "
"serveur de courriel, etc."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:60(para)
msgid ""
"The requirements for UEC are slightly different for Front End requirements "
"see <xref linkend=\"uec-frontend-requirements\"/> and for UEC Node "
"requirements see <xref linkend=\"uec-node-requirements\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:68(title)
msgid "Server and Desktop Differences"
msgstr "Différences entre la version serveur et la version Desktop"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:69(para)
msgid ""
"There are a few differences between the <emphasis>Ubuntu Server "
"Edition</emphasis> and the <emphasis>Ubuntu Desktop Edition</emphasis>. It "
"should be noted that both editions use the same "
"<application>apt</application> repositories. Making it just as easy to "
"install a <emphasis role=\"italic\">server</emphasis> application on the "
"Desktop Edition as it is on the Server Edition."
msgstr ""
"Peu de choses différencient <emphasis>l'édition serveur d'Ubuntu</emphasis> "
"de <emphasis>l'édition poste de travail d'Ubuntu</emphasis> (desktop). Les "
"deux versions utilisent les mêmes dépôts <application>apt</application>, ce "
"qui rend l'installation de programmes <emphasis "
"role=\"italic\">serveur</emphasis> aussi aisée sous l'édition desktop que "
"sous l'édition serveur."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:75(para)
msgid ""
"The differences between the two editions are the lack of an X window "
"environment in the Server Edition, the installation process, and different "
"Kernel options."
msgstr ""
"Les différences essentielles entre les deux versions résident dans l'absence "
"d'environnement « X window » dans l'édition serveur, le processus "
"d'installation et des options différentes pour le noyau."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:82(title)
msgid "Kernel Differences:"
msgstr "Différences concernant le noyau :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:85(para)
msgid ""
"The Server Edition uses the <emphasis>Deadline</emphasis> I/O scheduler "
"instead of the <emphasis>CFQ</emphasis> scheduler used by the Desktop "
"Edition."
msgstr ""
"L'édition serveur utilise l'ordonnanceur d'entrées/sorties "
"<emphasis>Deadline</emphasis> au lieu de <emphasis>CFQ</emphasis> pour "
"l'édition poste de travail."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:91(para)
msgid "<emphasis>Preemption</emphasis> is turned off in the Server Edition."
msgstr ""
"La <emphasis>préemption</emphasis> est désactivé dans l'édition serveur."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:96(para)
msgid ""
"The timer interrupt is 100 Hz in the Server Edition and 250 Hz in the "
"Desktop Edition."
msgstr ""
"La fréquence des interruptions est de 100 Hz dans la version serveur et de "
"250 Hz dans la version Desktop."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:102(para)
msgid ""
"When running a 64-bit version of Ubuntu on 64-bit processors you are not "
"limited by memory addressing space."
msgstr ""
"Quand vous exécutez une version 64-bit d'Ubuntu sur un processeur 64-bit "
"vous n'êtes pas limité par l'espace d'adressage mémoire."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:107(para)
msgid ""
"To see all kernel configuration options you can look through "
"<filename>/boot/config-2.6.31-server</filename>. Also, <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kroah.com/lkn/\">Linux Kernel in a Nutshell</ulink> is a "
"great resource on the options available."
msgstr ""
"Pour voir toutes les options de configuration du noyau, vous pouvez regarder "
"dans le fichier <filename>/boot/config-2.6.31-server</filename>. De plus, "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.kroah.com/lkn/\">le noyau Linux en quelques mots (en "
"anglais)</ulink> est une bonne ressource pour connaître les options "
"disponibles."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:116(title)
msgid "Backing Up"
msgstr "Sauvegarde"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:119(para)
msgid ""
"Before installing <application>Ubuntu Server Edition</application> you "
"should make sure all data on the system is backed up. See <xref "
"linkend=\"backups\"/> for backup options."
msgstr ""
"Avant d'installer <application>Ubuntu édition serveur</application> vous "
"devez être certain que toutes les données de votre système sont "
"sauvegardées. Voir <xref linkend=\"backups\"/> pour les options de "
"sauvegarde."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:123(para)
msgid ""
"If this is not the first time an operating system has been installed on your "
"computer, it is likely you will need to re-partition your disk to make room "
"for Ubuntu."
msgstr ""
"Si ce n'est pas le premier système d'exploitation installé sur votre "
"ordinateur, il se pourrait que vous ayez à re-partitionner votre disque dur "
"afin de faire de la place pour Ubuntu."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:127(para)
msgid ""
"Any time you partition your disk, you should be prepared to lose everything "
"on the disk should you make a mistake or something goes wrong during "
"partitioning. The programs used in installation are quite reliable, most "
"have seen years of use, but they also perform destructive actions."
msgstr ""
"A chaque fois que vous partitionnez votre disque dur, vous devez être "
"conscient que vous pouvez effacer toutes les données de votre disque dur, "
"faire une erreur ou que quelque chose se passe mal durant le "
"partitionnement. Les programmes utilisés dans l'installation sont fiables, "
"la plupart sont utilisés depuis de nombreuses années, mais ils sont capables "
"d'effectuer des actions destructrices."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:139(title)
msgid "Installing from CD"
msgstr "Installation à partir du CD"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:140(para)
msgid ""
"The basic steps to install Ubuntu Server Edition from CD are the same for "
"installing any operating system from CD. Unlike the <emphasis>Desktop "
"Edition</emphasis> the <emphasis>Server Edition</emphasis> does not include "
"a graphical installation program. Instead the Server Edition uses a console "
"menu based process."
msgstr ""
"Les étapes basiques pour installer Ubuntu édition serveur à partir du CD "
"sont les mêmes que pour l'installation de n'importe quel système "
"d'exploitation à partir d'un CD. Contrairement à l'<emphasis>édition "
"Desktop</emphasis> l'<emphasis>édition serveur</emphasis> n'inclut pas de "
"programme d'installation graphique. À la place, l'édition serveur s'installe "
"en mode console."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:147(para)
msgid ""
"First, download and burn the appropriate ISO file from the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/getubuntu/download\"> Ubuntu web site</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Tout d'abord, telechargez et gravez le fichier ISO approprié à partir du "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/getubuntu/download\">site Web "
"d'Ubuntu</ulink>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:153(para)
msgid "Boot the system from the CD-ROM drive."
msgstr "Démarrer le système depuis le lecteur CD."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:158(para)
msgid ""
"At the boot prompt you will be asked to select the language. Afterwards the "
"installation process begins by asking for your keyboard layout."
msgstr ""
"À l'invite de commande de démarrage il vous sera demandé de sélectionner "
"votre langue. Le processus d'installation débutera ensuite en vous demandant "
"la disposition de votre clavier."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:164(para)
msgid ""
"From the main boot menu there are some additional options to install Ubuntu "
"Server Edition. You can install a basic Ubuntu Server, or install Ubuntu "
"Server as part of a <emphasis>Ubuntu Enterprise Cloud</emphasis>. For more "
"information on UEC see <xref linkend=\"uec\"/>. The rest of this section "
"will cover the basic Ubuntu Server install."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:172(para)
msgid ""
"The installer then discovers your hardware configuration, and configures the "
"network settings using DHCP. If you do not wish to use DHCP at the next "
"screen choose \"Go Back\", and you have the option to \"Configure the "
"network manually\"."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:179(para)
msgid "Next, the installer asks for the system's hostname and Time Zone."
msgstr ""
"Ensuite, l'installateur vous demande de renseigner le nom de votre machine "
"ainsi que le fuseau horaire."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:184(para)
msgid ""
"You can then choose from several options to configure the hard drive layout. "
"For advanced disk options see <xref linkend=\"advanced-installation\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Plusieurs options sont disponibles pour l'agencement du disque dur. "
"Consultez <xref linkend=\"advanced-installation\"/> pour les options "
"avancées concernant les disques durs."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:190(para)
msgid "The Ubuntu base system is then installed."
msgstr "Le système Ubuntu de base est maintenant installée."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:195(para)
msgid ""
"A new user is setup, this user will have <emphasis>root</emphasis> access "
"through the <application>sudo</application> utility."
msgstr ""
"Un nouvel utilisateur est créé, cet utilisateur aura un accès "
"<emphasis>administratif</emphasis> (root) en utilisant l'application "
"<application>sudo</application>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:201(para)
msgid ""
"After the user is setup, you will be asked to encrypt your <filename "
"role=\"directory\">home</filename> directory."
msgstr ""
"Après la définition de l'utilisateur, il vous sera demandé de chiffrer votre "
"<filename role=\"directory\">dossier personnel</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:207(para)
msgid ""
"The next step in the installation process is to decide how you want to "
"update the system. There are three options:"
msgstr ""
"La prochaine étape vous proposera de mettre à jour le système. Trois options "
"sont possibles :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:213(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>No automatic updates</emphasis>: this requires an administrator to "
"log into the machine and manually install updates."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Pas de mises à jour automatiques</emphasis> : un administrateur "
"devra se connecter à la machine et effectuer les mises à jour manuellement."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:219(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Install security updates Automatically</emphasis>: will install "
"the <application>unattended-upgrades</application> package, which will "
"install security updates without the intervention of an administrator. For "
"more details see <xref linkend=\"automatic-updates\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Installer les mises à jours de sécurité "
"automatiquement</emphasis> : le paquet <application>unattended-"
"upgrades</application> sera installé. Il permet l'installation des mises à "
"jour de sécurité sans intervention humaine. Consultez <xref "
"linkend=\"automatic-updates\"/> pour de plus amples informations."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:226(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Manage the system with Landscape</emphasis>: Landscape is a paid "
"service provided by Canonical to help manage your Ubuntu machines. See the "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.canonical.com/projects/landscape\">Landscape</ulink> "
"site for details."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Gérer le système avec Landscape</emphasis>: Landscape est un "
"service payant proposé par Canonical pour aider à gérer vos machines Ubuntu. "
"Voir le site <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.canonical.com/projects/landscape\">Landscape</ulink> (en "
"anglais) pour plus de détails."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:235(para)
msgid ""
"You now have the option to install, or not install, several package tasks. "
"See <xref linkend=\"install-tasks\"/> for details. Also, there is an option "
"to launch <application>aptitude</application> to choose specific packages to "
"install. For more information see <xref linkend=\"aptitude\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Vous avez maintenant la possibilité d'installer ou de ne pas installer "
"plusieurs paquets de tâches. Voir <xref linkend=\"install-tasks\"/> pour "
"plus de détails. Il existe aussi une option pour lancer "
"<application>aptitude</application> afin de choisir les paquets à installer. "
"Pour de plus amples informations, voir <xref linkend=\"aptitude\"/>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:243(para)
msgid "Finally, the last step before rebooting is to set the clock to UTC."
msgstr ""
"Finalement, la dernière étape avant de redémarrer le système est "
"d'initialiser l'horloge sur UTC."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:249(para)
msgid ""
"If at any point during installation you are not satisfied by the default "
"setting, use the \"Go Back\" function at any prompt to be brought to a "
"detailed installation menu that will allow you to modify the default "
"settings."
msgstr ""
"Si à un moment quelconque de l'installation vous n'êtes pas satisfait de la "
"configuration par défaut, vous pouvez utiliser la fonction « Précédent » qui "
"vous présentera un menu d'installation plus détaillé permettant de modifier "
"les options par défaut."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:254(para)
msgid ""
"At some point during the installation process you may want to read the help "
"screen provided by the installation system. To do this, press F1."
msgstr ""
"A n'importe quel moment durant le processus d'installation vous pouvez avoir "
"envie d'accéder à l'écran d'aide fournit par le système d'installation. Pour "
"ce faire, appuyez sur F1."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:259(para)
msgid ""
"Once again, for detailed instructions see the <ulink "
"url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/10.04 LTS/installation-guide/\"> Ubuntu "
"Installation Guide</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:265(title)
msgid "Package Tasks"
msgstr "Paquet de fonctionnalités"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:266(para)
msgid ""
"During the Server Edition installation you have the option of installing "
"additional packages from the CD. The packages are grouped by the type of "
"service they provide."
msgstr ""
"Pendant l'installation de l'édition serveur vous avez la possibilité "
"d'installer des paquets supplémentaires à partir du CD. Ces paquets sont "
"regroupés en fonction du type de service qu'ils fournissent."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:272(para)
msgid "Cloud computing: Walrus storage service"
msgstr "Nuage informatique : service de stockage Walrus"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:277(para)
msgid "Cloud computing: all-in-one cluster"
msgstr "Nuage informatique : grappe tout-en-un"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:282(para)
msgid "Cloud computing: Cluster controller"
msgstr "Nuage informatique : contrôleur de grappe"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:287(para)
msgid "Cloud computing: Node controller"
msgstr "Nuage informatique : contrôleur de nœud"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:292(para)
msgid "Cloud computing: Storage controller"
msgstr "Nuage informatique : contrôleur de stockage"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:297(para)
msgid "Cloud computing: top-level cloud controller"
msgstr "Nuage informatique : contrôleur de nuage de haut niveau"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:302(para)
msgid "DNS server: Selects the BIND DNS server and its documentation."
msgstr "Serveur DNS : Sélectionne le serveur DNS BIND et sa documentation."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:307(para)
msgid "LAMP server: Selects a ready-made Linux/Apache/MySQL/PHP server."
msgstr ""
"Serveur LAMP : Sélectionne un serveur Linux/Apache/MySQL/PHP prêt à utiliser."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:312(para)
msgid ""
"Mail server: This task selects a variety of package useful for a general "
"purpose mail server system."
msgstr ""
"Serveur mail : Cette tâche sélectionne une variété de paquets utiles pour un "
"système de serveur mail à usage généraliste."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:317(para)
msgid "OpenSSH server: Selects packages needed for an OpenSSH server."
msgstr ""
"Serveur OpenSSH: Sélectionne les paquets nécessaires pour un serveur OpenSSH."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:322(para)
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL database: This task selects client and server packages for the "
"PostgreSQL database."
msgstr ""
"Base de données PostgreSQL : cette tâche sélectionne les paquets client et "
"serveur pour la base de données PostgreSQL."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:327(para)
msgid "Print server: This task sets up your system to be a print server."
msgstr ""
"Serveur d'impression : cette tâche configure votre système pour qu'il "
"devienne un serveur d'impression."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:332(para)
msgid ""
"Samba File server: This task sets up your system to be a Samba file server, "
"which is especially suitable in networks with both Windows and Linux systems."
msgstr ""
"Serveur de fichiers Samba : cette tâche installe un serveur de fichiers "
"Samba, qui est particulièrement adapté aux réseaux hétérogènes Windows et "
"Linux."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:338(para)
msgid ""
"Tomcat server: Installs the Apache Tomcat and needed dependencies Java, gcj, "
"etc."
msgstr ""
"Serveur Tomcat : installe le serveur Apache Tomcat et les dépendances "
"idoines (java, gcj, etc.)"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:343(para)
msgid ""
"Virtual machine host: Includes packages needed to run KVM virtual machines."
msgstr ""
"Hôte de machine virtuelle : inclut les paquets nécessaires pour lancer les "
"machines virtuelles KVM."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:348(para)
msgid ""
"Manually select packages: Executes <application>apptitude</application> "
"allowing you to individually select packages."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:353(para)
msgid ""
"Installing the package groups is accomplished using the "
"<application>tasksel</application> utility. One of the important difference "
"between Ubuntu (or Debian) and other GNU/Linux distribution is that, when "
"installed, a package is also configured to reasonable defaults, eventually "
"prompting you for additional required information. Likewise, when installing "
"a task, the packages are not only installed, but also configured to provided "
"a fully integrated service."
msgstr ""
"L'utilitaire <application>tasksel</application> permet d'installer des "
"groupes de paquets. Une des différences importante entre Ubuntu (ou Debian) "
"et les autres distributions GNU/Linux est que, quand un paquet est installé, "
"il est aussi configuré avec des options raisonnables par défaut, "
"éventuellement en vous demandant des informations requises supplémentaires. "
"Ainsi lorsque vous installez une fonctionnalité (avec taskel) , les paquets "
"ne sont pas seulement installés mais aussi configurés pour fournir un "
"service totalement intégré."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:360(para)
msgid ""
"For more information on the <emphasis>Cloud Computing</emphasis> tasks see "
"<xref linkend=\"uec\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Pour plus d'informations sur tout ce qui concerne les <emphasis>nuages "
"informatiques</emphasis>, consultez <xref linkend=\"uec\"/>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:363(para)
msgid ""
"Once the installation process has finished you can view a list of available "
"tasks by entering the following from a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Une fois le processus d'installation terminé vous pouvez obtenir une liste "
"des tâches disponibles en saisissant la commande suivante depuis un "
"terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:368(command)
msgid "tasksel --list-tasks"
msgstr "tasksel --list-tasks"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:371(para)
msgid ""
"The output will list tasks from other Ubuntu based distributions such as "
"Kubuntu and Edubuntu. Note that you can also invoke the "
"<command>tasksel</command> command by itself, which will bring up a menu of "
"the different tasks available."
msgstr ""
"Le résultat de cette commande listera les tâches des autres distributions "
"basées sur Ubuntu comme Kubuntu et Edubuntu. Remarquez que vous pouvez aussi "
"appeler la commande <command>tasksel</command> seule afin d'obtenir un menu "
"des différentes tâches disponibles."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:377(para)
msgid ""
"You can view a list of which packages are installed with each task using the "
"<emphasis>--task-packages</emphasis> option. For example, to list the "
"packages installed with the <emphasis>DNS Server</emphasis> task enter the "
"following:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez voir une liste des paquets qui sont installés pour chaque tâche "
"en utilisant l'option <emphasis>--task-packages</emphasis>. Par exemple, "
"pour lister les paquets installés avec la tâche du <emphasis>serveur "
"DNS</emphasis> saisissez ce qui suit :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:382(command)
msgid "tasksel --task-packages dns-server"
msgstr "tasksel --task-packages dns-server"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:384(para)
msgid "The output of the command should list:"
msgstr "Le résultat de cette commande doit lister :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:387(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"bind9-doc \n"
"bind9utils \n"
"bind9\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"bind9-doc \n"
"bind9utils \n"
"bind9\n"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:392(para)
msgid ""
"Also, if you did not install one of the tasks during the installation "
"process, but for example you decide to make your new LAMP server a DNS "
"server as well. Simply insert the installation CD and from a terminal:"
msgstr ""
"Si vous n'avez pas installé une des tâches durant le processus "
"d'installation, mais que par exemple vous décidez de faire de votre serveur "
"LAMP également un serveur DNS, insérez simplement le CD d'installation et "
"exécutez dans un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:397(command)
msgid "sudo tasksel install dns-server"
msgstr "sudo tasksel install dns-server"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:402(title)
msgid "Upgrading"
msgstr "Mise à niveau"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:403(para)
msgid ""
"There are several ways to upgrade from one Ubuntu release to another. This "
"section gives an overview of the recommended upgrade method."
msgstr ""
"Il y a plusieurs façons de migrer d'une version d'Ubuntu vers une autre. "
"Cette section donne un aperçu des méthodes de mises à niveau recommandées."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:407(title) serverguide/C/installation.xml:422(command)
msgid "do-release-upgrade"
msgstr "do-release-upgrade"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:408(para)
msgid ""
"The recommended way to upgrade a Server Edition installation is to use the "
"<application>do-release-upgrade</application> utility. Part of the "
"<emphasis>update-manager-core</emphasis> package, it does not have any "
"graphical dependencies and is installed by default."
msgstr ""
"La manière recommandée pour mettre à jour une installation d'une édition "
"serveur est l'utilisation de <application>do-release-upgrade</application>. "
"C'est un composant du paquet <emphasis>update-manager-core</emphasis>, qui "
"ne dépend d'aucun gestionnaire graphique et qui est installé par défaut."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:413(para)
msgid ""
"Debian based systems can also be upgraded by using <command>apt-get dist-"
"upgrade</command>. However, using <application>do-release-"
"upgrade</application> is recommended because it has the ability to handle "
"system configuration changes sometimes needed between releases."
msgstr ""
"Les systèmes basés sur Debian peuvent aussi être mis à jour en utilisant la "
"commande <command>apt-get dist-upgrade</command>. Cependant, l'utilisation "
"de <application>do-release-upgrade</application> est recommandée car elle a "
"la possibilité de gérer les changements de la configuration système "
"nécessaires entre chaque versions."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:418(para)
msgid "To upgrade to a newer release, from a terminal prompt enter:"
msgstr ""
"Pour mettre à jour vers une nouvelle version, saisissez dans un terminal :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:424(para)
msgid ""
"It is also possible to use <application>do-release-upgrade</application> to "
"upgrade to a development version of Ubuntu. To accomplish this use the "
"<emphasis>-d</emphasis> switch:"
msgstr ""
"Il est également possible d'utiliser <application>do-release-"
"upgrade</application> pour mettre à jour vers une version d'Ubuntu en cours "
"de développement. Pour ce faire utilisez l'option <emphasis>-d</emphasis> :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:429(command)
msgid "do-release-upgrade -d"
msgstr "do-release-upgrade -d"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:432(para)
msgid ""
"Upgrading to a development release is <emphasis>not</emphasis> recommended "
"for production environments."
msgstr ""
"Mettre à jour vers une version en cours de développement <emphasis>n'est "
"pas</emphasis> recommandé pour les environnements de production."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:439(title)
msgid "Advanced Installation"
msgstr "Installation avancée"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:442(title)
msgid "Software RAID"
msgstr "RAID logiciel"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:444(para)
msgid ""
"RAID is a method of configuring multiple hard drives to act as one, reducing "
"the probability of catastrophic data loss in case of drive failure. RAID is "
"implemented in either software (where the operating system knows about both "
"drives and actively maintains both of them) or hardware (where a special "
"controller makes the OS think there's only one drive and maintains the "
"drives 'invisibly')."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:451(para)
msgid ""
"The RAID software included with current versions of Linux (and Ubuntu) is "
"based on the <application>'mdadm'</application> driver and works very well, "
"better even than many so-called 'hardware' RAID controllers. This section "
"will guide you through installing Ubuntu Server Edition using two RAID1 "
"partitions on two physical hard drives, one for <emphasis>/</emphasis> and "
"another for <emphasis>swap</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:461(para) serverguide/C/installation.xml:975(para)
msgid ""
"Follow the installation steps until you get to the <emphasis>Partition "
"disks</emphasis> step, then:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:468(para)
msgid "Select <emphasis>Manual</emphasis> as the partition method."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez <emphasis>Manuel</emphasis> comme méthode de partitionnement."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:475(para)
msgid ""
"Select the first hard drive, and agree to <emphasis>\"Create a new empty "
"partition table on this device?\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:479(para)
msgid ""
"Repeat this step for each drive you wish to be part of the RAID array."
msgstr ""
"Répétez cette étape pour chaque disque que vous souhaitez inclure dans la "
"matrice RAID."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:486(para)
msgid ""
"Select the <emphasis>\"FREE SPACE\"</emphasis> on the first drive then "
"select <emphasis>\"Create a new partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:493(para)
msgid ""
"Next, select the <emphasis>Size</emphasis> of the partition. This partition "
"will be the <emphasis>swap</emphasis> partition, and a general rule for swap "
"size is twice that of RAM. Enter the partition size, then choose "
"<emphasis>Primary</emphasis>, then <emphasis>Beginning</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:502(para)
msgid ""
"Select the <emphasis>\"Use as:\"</emphasis> line at the top. By default this "
"is <emphasis role=\"italic\">\"Ext4 journaling file system\"</emphasis>, "
"change that to <emphasis>\"physical volume for RAID\"</emphasis> then "
"<emphasis>\"Done setting up partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:511(para)
msgid ""
"For the <emphasis>/</emphasis> partition once again select <emphasis>\"Free "
"Space\"</emphasis> on the first drive then <emphasis>\"Create a new "
"partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:519(para)
msgid ""
"Use the rest of the free space on the drive and choose "
"<emphasis>Continue</emphasis>, then <emphasis>Primary</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:526(para)
msgid ""
"As with the swap partition, select the <emphasis>\"Use as:\"</emphasis> line "
"at the top, changing it to <emphasis>\"physical volume for "
"RAID\"</emphasis>. Also select the <emphasis>\"Bootable flag:\"</emphasis> "
"line to change the value to <emphasis>\"on\"</emphasis>. Then choose "
"<emphasis>\"Done setting up partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:536(para)
msgid "Repeat steps three through eight for the other disk and partitions."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:545(title)
msgid "RAID Configuration"
msgstr "Configuration du RAID"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:547(para)
msgid "With the partitions setup the arrays are ready to be configured:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:554(para)
msgid ""
"Back in the main \"Partition Disks\" page, select <emphasis>\"Configure "
"Software RAID\"</emphasis> at the top."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:561(para)
msgid "Select <emphasis>\"yes\"</emphasis> to write the changes to disk."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:568(para)
msgid "Choose <emphasis>\"Create MD device\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:575(para)
msgid ""
"For this example, select <emphasis>\"RAID1\"</emphasis>, but if you are "
"using a different setup choose the appropriate type (RAID0 RAID1 RAID5)."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:581(para)
msgid ""
"In order to use <emphasis>RAID5</emphasis> you need at least "
"<emphasis>three</emphasis> drives. Using RAID0 or RAID1 only "
"<emphasis>two</emphasis> drives are required."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:590(para)
msgid ""
"Enter the number of active devices <emphasis>\"2\"</emphasis>, or the amount "
"of hard drives you have, for the array. Then select "
"<emphasis>\"Continue\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:598(para)
msgid ""
"Next, enter the number of spare devices <emphasis>\"0\"</emphasis> by "
"default, then choose <emphasis>\"Continue\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:605(para)
msgid ""
"Choose which partitions to use. Generally they will be sda1, sdb1, sdc1, "
"etc. The numbers will usually match and the different letters correspond to "
"different hard drives."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:610(para)
msgid ""
"For the <emphasis>swap</emphasis> partition choose <emphasis>sda1</emphasis> "
"and <emphasis>sdb1</emphasis>. Select <emphasis>\"Continue\"</emphasis> to "
"go to the next step."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:618(para)
msgid ""
"Repeat steps <emphasis>three</emphasis> through <emphasis>seven</emphasis> "
"for the <emphasis>/</emphasis> partition choosing <emphasis>sda2</emphasis> "
"and <emphasis>sdb2</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:626(para)
msgid "Once done select <emphasis>\"Finish\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:636(title)
msgid "Formatting"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:638(para)
msgid ""
"There should now be a list of hard drives and RAID devices. The next step is "
"to format and set the mount point for the RAID devices. Treat the RAID "
"device as a local hard drive, format and mount accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Vous avez maintenant une liste des disques durs ainsi que celle des "
"périphériques RAID. Il faut alors les formater et leur assigner le(s) "
"point(s) de montage. Considérez les ensembles RAID comme des partitions "
"normales en ce qui concerne le formatage et le montage."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:646(para)
msgid ""
"Select <emphasis>\"#1\"</emphasis> under the <emphasis>\"RAID1 device "
"#0\"</emphasis> partition."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:653(para)
msgid ""
"Choose <emphasis>\"Use as:\"</emphasis>. Then select <emphasis>\"swap "
"area\"</emphasis>, then <emphasis>\"Done setting up partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez <emphasis>Utiliser comme :</emphasis> suivi de <emphasis>espace "
"d'échange (swap)</emphasis> puis <emphasis>Fin de paramétrage de cette "
"partition</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:661(para)
msgid ""
"Next, select <emphasis>\"#1\"</emphasis> under the <emphasis>\"RAID1 device "
"#1\"</emphasis> partition."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:668(para)
msgid ""
"Choose <emphasis>\"Use as:\"</emphasis>. Then select <emphasis>\"Ext4 "
"journaling file system\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:675(para)
msgid ""
"Then select the <emphasis>\"Mount point\"</emphasis> and choose "
"<emphasis>\"/ - the root file system\"</emphasis>. Change any of the other "
"options as appropriate, then select <emphasis>\"Done setting up "
"partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez <emphasis>Point de montage</emphasis> suivi de <emphasis>/ - "
"système de fichiers racine</emphasis>. Sélectionnez <emphasis>Fin de "
"paramétrage de cette partition</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:683(para)
msgid ""
"Finally, select <emphasis>\"Finish partitioning and write changes to "
"disk\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Pour finir sélectionnez <emphasis>Fin de paramétrage de cette partition et "
"appliquer les changements</emphasis> puis répondez <emphasis>Oui</emphasis>"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:690(para)
msgid ""
"If you choose to place the root partition on a RAID array, the installer "
"will then ask if you would like to boot in a <emphasis>degraded</emphasis> "
"state. See <xref linkend=\"raid-degraded\"/> for further details."
msgstr ""
"Si vous choisissez de placer la partition racine sur une matrice RAID, "
"l'installateur vous demandera alors si vous voulez démarrer dans un état "
"RAID <emphasis>dégradé</emphasis>. Consultez <xref linkend=\"raid-"
"degraded\"/> pour plus de renseignements."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:695(para)
msgid "The installation process will then continue normally."
msgstr "Le processus d'installation continuera ensuite normalement."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:701(title)
msgid "Degraded RAID"
msgstr "RAIS dégradé"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:703(para)
msgid ""
"At some point in the life of the computer a disk failure event may occur. "
"When this happens, using Software RAID, the operating system will place the "
"array into what is known as a <emphasis>degraded</emphasis> state."
msgstr ""
"Au cours de la vie d'un ordinateur, une panne de disque dur peut survenir. "
"Lorsque ceci arrive avec du RAID logiciel, les système d'exploitation "
"placera la matrice RAID dans un état que l'on appelle "
"<emphasis>dégradé</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:708(para)
msgid ""
"If the array has become degraded, due to the chance of data corruption, by "
"default Ubuntu Server Edition will boot to <emphasis>initramfs</emphasis> "
"after thirty seconds. Once the initramfs has booted there is a fifteen "
"second prompt giving you the option to go ahead and boot the system, or "
"attempt manual recover. Booting to the initramfs prompt may or may not be "
"the desired behavior, especially if the machine is in a remote location. "
"Booting to a degraded array can be configured several ways:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:719(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>dpkg-reconfigure</application> utility can be used to "
"configure the default behavior, and during the process you will be queried "
"about additional settings related to the array. Such as monitoring, email "
"alerts, etc. To reconfigure <application>mdadm</application> enter the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:726(command)
msgid "sudo dpkg-reconfigure mdadm"
msgstr "sudo dpkg-reconfigure mdadm"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:732(para)
msgid ""
"The <command>dpkg-reconfigure mdadm</command> process will change the "
"<filename>/etc/initramfs-tools/conf.d/mdadm</filename> configuration file. "
"The file has the advantage of being able to pre-configure the system's "
"behavior, and can also be manually edited:"
msgstr ""
"Le processus <command>dpkg-reconfigure mdadm</command> changera le contenu "
"du fichier de configuration <filename>/etc/initramfs-"
"tools/conf.d/mdadm</filename>. Ce fichier a l'avantage de pouvoir pré-"
"configurer le comportement de votre système et il peut également être "
"modifié manuellement :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:738(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"BOOT_DEGRADED=true\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"BOOT_DEGRADED=true\n"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:743(para)
msgid "The configuration file can be overridden by using a Kernel argument."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:751(para)
msgid ""
"Using a Kernel argument will allow the system to boot to a degraded array as "
"well:"
msgstr ""
"Donner un argument au noyau autorisera également le système à démarrer sur "
"une matrice RAID endommagée :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:757(para)
msgid ""
"When the server is booting press <keycap>Shift</keycap> to open the "
"<application>Grub</application> menu."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:762(para)
msgid "Press <keycap>e</keycap> to edit your kernel command options."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:767(para)
msgid "Press the <keycap>down</keycap> arrow to highlight the kernel line."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:772(para)
msgid ""
"Add <emphasis>\"bootdegraded=true\"</emphasis> (without the quotes) to the "
"end of the line."
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez <emphasis>\"bootdegraded=true\"</emphasis> (sans les guillemets) en "
"fin de ligne."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:777(para)
msgid ""
"Press <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>x</keycap></keycombo> to boot "
"the system."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:786(para)
msgid ""
"Once the system has booted you can either repair the array see <xref "
"linkend=\"raid-maintenance\"/> for details, or copy important data to "
"another machine due to major hardware failure."
msgstr ""
"Une fois le système démarré, vous pouvez réparer la matrice (voir <xref "
"linkend=\"raid-maintenance\"/> pour de plus amples informations) ou "
"transférez les données importantes vers un autre machine en cas de panne "
"matérielle majeure."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:793(title)
msgid "RAID Maintenance"
msgstr "Maintenance RAID"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:795(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>mdadm</application> utility can be used to view the status "
"of an array, add disks to an array, remove disks, etc:"
msgstr ""
"L'utilitaire <application>mdadm</application> peut être utilisé pour "
"afficher l'état d'une matrice, ajouter des disques à une matrice, en "
"supprimer etc... :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:802(para)
msgid "To view the status of an array, from a terminal prompt enter:"
msgstr "Pour afficher l'état d'une matrice, depuis un terminal entrez :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:806(command)
msgid "sudo mdadm -D /dev/md0"
msgstr "sudo mdadm -D /dev/md0"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:809(para)
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>-D</emphasis> tells <application>mdadm</application> to "
"display <emphasis>detailed</emphasis> information about the "
"<filename>/dev/md0</filename> device. Replace <filename>/dev/md0</filename> "
"with the appropriate RAID device."
msgstr ""
"L'option <emphasis>-D</emphasis> ordonne à <application>mdadm</application> "
"d'afficher les informations <emphasis>détaillées</emphasis>  du périphérique "
"<filename>/dev/md0</filename>. Remplacez <filename>/dev/md0</filename> par "
"le périphérique RAID souhaité."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:815(para)
msgid "To view the status of a disk in an array:"
msgstr "Pour afficher l'état d'un disque d'une matrice, écrivez :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:819(command)
msgid "sudo mdadm -E /dev/sda1"
msgstr "sudo mdadm -E /dev/sda1"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:821(para)
msgid ""
"The output if very similar to the <command>mdadm -D</command> command, "
"adjust <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> for each disk."
msgstr ""
"Le résultat est très similaire à celui de la commande <command>mdadm -"
"D</command>, modifiez <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> à votre convenance pour "
"chaque disque."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:826(para)
msgid "If a disk fails and needs to be removed from an array enter:"
msgstr ""
"Si un disque devient défectueux et doit être retiré d'une matrice, entrez :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:830(command)
msgid "sudo mdadm --remove /dev/md0 /dev/sda1"
msgstr "sudo mdadm --remove /dev/md0 /dev/sda1"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:832(para)
msgid ""
"Change <filename>/dev/md0</filename> and <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> to "
"the appropriate RAID device and disk."
msgstr ""
"Changez <filename>/dev/md0</filename> et <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> par "
"les périphériques et les disques RAID appropriés."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:837(para)
msgid "Similarly, to add a new disk:"
msgstr "De la même manière, pour ajouter un disque :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:841(command)
msgid "sudo mdadm --add /dev/md0 /dev/sda1"
msgstr "sudo mdadm --add /dev/md0 /dev/sda1"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:846(para)
msgid ""
"Sometimes a disk can change to a <emphasis>faulty</emphasis> state even "
"though there is nothing physically wrong with the drive. It is usually "
"worthwhile to remove the drive from the array then re-add it. This will "
"cause the drive to re-sync with the array. If the drive will not sync with "
"the array, it is a good indication of hardware failure."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:852(para)
msgid ""
"The <filename>/proc/mdstat</filename> file also contains useful information "
"about the system's RAID devices:"
msgstr ""
"Le fichier <filename>/proc/mdstat</filename> contient également des "
"informations utiles concernant les périphériques RAID du système."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:857(command)
msgid "cat /proc/mdstat"
msgstr "cat /proc/mdstat"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:858(computeroutput)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Personalities : [linear] [multipath] [raid0] [raid1] [raid6] [raid5] [raid4] "
"[raid10] \n"
"md0 : active raid1 sda1[0] sdb1[1]\n"
"      10016384 blocks [2/2] [UU]\n"
"      \n"
"unused devices: &lt;none&gt;"
msgstr ""
"Personalities : [linear] [multipath] [raid0] [raid1] [raid6] [raid5] [raid4] "
"[raid10] \n"
"md0 : active raid1 sda1[0] sdb1[1]\n"
"      10016384 blocks [2/2] [UU]\n"
"      \n"
"unused devices: &lt;none&gt;"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:865(para)
msgid ""
"The following command is great for watching the status of a syncing drive:"
msgstr ""
"La commande suivante est très utile pour surveiller l'état d'avancement "
"d'une synchronisation de disque :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:870(command)
msgid "watch -n1 cat /proc/mdstat"
msgstr "watch -n1 cat /proc/mdstat"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:873(para)
msgid ""
"Press <emphasis>Ctrl+c</emphasis> to stop the "
"<application>watch</application> command."
msgstr ""
"Appuyez sur <emphasis>Ctrl+c</emphasis> pour arrêter la commande "
"<application>watch</application>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:877(para)
msgid ""
"If you do need to replace a faulty drive, after the drive has been replaced "
"and synced, <application>grub</application> will need to be installed. To "
"install <application>grub</application> on the new drive, enter the "
"following:"
msgstr ""
"Une fois qu'un disque défectueux a été remplacé par un disque en bon état et "
"que celui-ci a été synchronisé, vous devez installer "
"<application>grub</application>. Pour l'installer sur le nouveau disque, "
"saisissez :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:883(command)
msgid "sudo grub-install /dev/md0"
msgstr "sudo grub-install /dev/md0"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:886(para)
msgid ""
"Replace <filename>/dev/md0</filename> with the appropriate array device name."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:894(para)
msgid ""
"The topic of RAID arrays is a complex one due to the plethora of ways RAID "
"can be configured. Please see the following links for more information:"
msgstr ""
"Les matrices RAID sont un sujet complexe en raison de la multitude de façons "
"de paramétrer le RAID. Consultez les liens suivants pour plus "
"d'informations :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:901(para)
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Installation#raid\">Ubuntu "
"Wiki Articles on RAID</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:907(ulink)
msgid "Software RAID HOWTO"
msgstr "Guide pratique du RAID logiciel"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:912(ulink)
msgid "Managing RAID on Linux"
msgstr "Gérer le RAID sous LInux"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:919(title)
msgid "Logical Volume Manager (LVM)"
msgstr "Gestionnaire de volumes logiques (Logical Volume Manager, LVM)"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:921(para)
msgid ""
"Logical Volume Manger, or <emphasis>LVM</emphasis>, allows administrators to "
"create <emphasis>logical</emphasis> volumes out of one or multiple physical "
"hard disks. LVM volumes can be created on both software RAID partitions and "
"standard partitions residing on a single disk. Volumes can also be extended, "
"giving greater flexibility to systems as requirements change."
msgstr ""
"Le gestionnaire de volumes logiques, ou <emphasis>LVM</emphasis>, permet aux "
"administrateurs de créer des volumes <emphasis>logiques</emphasis> à partir "
"d'un ou plusieurs espaces de stockage. Les volumes LVM peuvent être créés "
"sur des partitions RAID logicielles ou sur des partitions normales résidant "
"sur un unique disque. Les volumes peuvent être dimensionnés après-coup, "
"donnant ainsi une plus grande flexibilité au système."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:930(para)
msgid ""
"A side effect of LVM's power and flexibility is a greater degree of "
"complication. Before diving into the LVM installation process, it is best to "
"get familiar with some terms."
msgstr ""
"Un effet secondaire de la puissance et de la flexibilité de LVM est un degré "
"accru de complexité. Avant de se plonger dans le processus d'installation de "
"LVM, il est préférable de se familiariser avec quelques termes techniques."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:937(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Volume Group (VG):</emphasis> contains one or several Logical "
"Volumes (LV)."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Groupe de volumes (Volume Group ou VG) :</emphasis> contient un ou "
"plusieurs volumes logiques (Logical Volumes ou LV)."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:942(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Logical Volume (LV):</emphasis> is similar to a partition in a non-"
"LVM system. Multiple Physical Volumes (PV) can make up one LV, on top of "
"which resides the actual EXT3, XFS, JFS, etc filesystem."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Volume Logique (Logical Volume ou LV) :</emphasis> similaire à une "
"partition d'un système non LVM. Plusieurs volumes physiques (Physical "
"Volumes ou PV) peuvent servir à créer un LV, au-dessus duquel réside le "
"véritable système de fichier EXT3, XFS, JFS, etc."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:948(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Physical Volume (PV):</emphasis> physical hard disk or software "
"RAID partition. The Volume Group can be extended by adding more PVs."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Volume physique (Physical Volume ou PV) :</emphasis> disque dur "
"physique ou partition logicielle RAID. Le groupe de volumes peut être "
"agrandi en ajoutant des PV."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:959(para)
msgid ""
"As an example this section covers installing Ubuntu Server Edition with "
"<filename role=\"directory\">/srv</filename> mounted on a LVM volume. During "
"the initial install only one Physical Volume (PV) will be part of the Volume "
"Group (VG). Another PV will be added after install to demonstrate how a VG "
"can be extended."
msgstr ""
"À titre d'exemple, cette section décrit l'installation d'Ubuntu édition "
"serveur en montant <filename role=\"directory\">/srv</filename> sur un "
"volume LVM. Lors de l'installation initiale, un seul volume physique (PV) "
"fera partie du groupe de volumes (VG). Un autre PV lui sera affecté plus "
"tard pour montrer comment un VG peut être agrandi."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:965(para)
msgid ""
"There are several installation options for LVM, <emphasis>\"Guided - use the "
"entire disk and setup LVM\"</emphasis> which will also allow you to assign a "
"portion of the available space to LVM, <emphasis>\"Guided - use entire and "
"setup encrypted LVM\"</emphasis>, or <emphasis>Manually</emphasis> setup the "
"partitions and configure LVM. At this time the only way to configure a "
"system with both LVM and standard partitions, during installation, is to use "
"the Manual approach."
msgstr ""
"Plusieurs méthodes d'installation sont disponibles pour LVM : "
"<emphasis>Assistée - utiliser tout un disque avec LVM</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Assistée - utiliser tout un disque avec LVM chiffré</emphasis> et "
"<emphasis>Manuelle</emphasis>. Pour l'instant l'approche manuelle est la "
"seule option nous permettant de paramétrer des partitions usuelles et LVM."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:982(para)
msgid ""
"At the <emphasis>\"Partition Disks</emphasis> screen choose "
"<emphasis>\"Manual\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez <emphasis>Manuel</emphasis> à l'étape <emphasis>Partitionner les "
"disques</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:989(para)
msgid ""
"Select the hard disk and on the next screen choose \"yes\" to "
"<emphasis>\"Create a new empty partition table on this device\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez votre disque et répondez oui à la question <emphasis>Faut-il "
"créer une nouvelle table de partitions sur ce disque</emphasis> de l'écran "
"suivant."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:996(para)
msgid ""
"Next, create standard <emphasis>/boot</emphasis>, <emphasis>swap</emphasis>, "
"and <emphasis>/</emphasis> partitions with whichever filesystem you prefer."
msgstr ""
"Créez ensuite trois partitions usuelles <emphasis>/boot</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>swap</emphasis> et <emphasis>/</emphasis> avec le système de "
"fichiers de votre choix."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1004(para)
msgid ""
"For the LVM <emphasis>/srv</emphasis>, create a new "
"<emphasis>Logical</emphasis> partition. Then change <emphasis>\"Use "
"as\"</emphasis> to <emphasis>\"physical volume for LVM\"</emphasis> then "
"<emphasis>\"Done setting up the partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1012(para)
msgid ""
"Now select <emphasis>\"Configure the Logical Volume Manager\"</emphasis> at "
"the top, and choose <emphasis>\"Yes\"</emphasis> to write the changes to "
"disk."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1020(para)
msgid ""
"For the <emphasis>\"LVM configuration action\"</emphasis> on the next "
"screen, choose <emphasis>\"Create volume group\"</emphasis>. Enter a name "
"for the VG such as <emphasis>vg01</emphasis>, or something more descriptive. "
"After entering a name, select the partition configured for LVM, and choose "
"<emphasis>\"Continue\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1029(para)
msgid ""
"Back at the <emphasis>\"LVM configuration action\"</emphasis> screen, select "
"<emphasis>\"Create logical volume\"</emphasis>. Select the newly created "
"volume group, and enter a name for the new LV, for example "
"<emphasis>srv</emphasis> since that is the intended mount point. Then choose "
"a size, which may be the full partition because it can always be extended "
"later. Choose <emphasis>\"Finish\"</emphasis> and you should be back at the "
"main <emphasis>\"Partition Disks\"</emphasis> screen."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1039(para)
msgid ""
"Now add a filesystem to the new LVM. Select the partition under "
"<emphasis>\"LVM VG vg01, LV srv\"</emphasis>, or whatever name you have "
"chosen, the choose <emphasis>Use as</emphasis>. Setup a file system as "
"normal selecting <emphasis>/srv</emphasis> as the mount point. Once done, "
"select <emphasis>\"Done setting up the partition\"</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1048(para)
msgid ""
"Finally, select <emphasis>\"Finish partitioning and write changes to "
"disk\"</emphasis>. Then confirm the changes and continue with the rest of "
"the installation."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1056(para)
msgid "There are some useful utilities to view information about LVM:"
msgstr ""
"Il existe des outils pratiques pour afficher des informations sur LVM :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1061(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>vgdisplay:</emphasis> shows information about Volume Groups."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>vgdisplay :</emphasis> affiche les informations des groupes de "
"volumes."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1062(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>lvdisplay:</emphasis> has information about Logical Volumes."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>lvdisplay :</emphasis> affiche les informations des volumes "
"logiques"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1063(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis>pvdisplay:</emphasis> similarly displays information about "
"Physical Volumes."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>pvdisplay :</emphasis> affiche les informations des volumes "
"physiques."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1068(title)
msgid "Extending Volume Groups"
msgstr "Agrandir des groupes de volumes"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1070(para)
msgid ""
"Continuing with <emphasis>srv</emphasis> as an LVM volume example, this "
"section covers adding a second hard disk, creating a Physical Volume (PV), "
"adding it to the volume group (VG), extending the logical volume <filename "
"role=\"directory\">srv</filename> and finally extending the filesystem. This "
"example assumes a second hard disk has been added to the system. This hard "
"disk will be named <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> in our example. BEWARE: "
"make sure you don't already have an existing <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> "
"before issuing the commands below. You could lose some data if you issue "
"those commands on a non-empty disk. In our example we will use the entire "
"disk as a physical volume (you could choose to create partitions and use "
"them as different physical volumes)"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1082(para)
msgid "First, create the physical volume, in a terminal execute:"
msgstr "Commencez par créer le volume physique. Depuis un terminal, lancez :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1087(command)
msgid "sudo pvcreate /dev/sdb"
msgstr "sudo pvcreate /dev/sdb"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1093(para)
msgid "Now extend the Volume Group (VG):"
msgstr "Agrandissez maintenant le groupe de volumes (VG) :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1098(command)
msgid "sudo vgextend vg01 /dev/sdb"
msgstr "sudo vgextend vg01 /dev/sdb"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1104(para)
msgid ""
"Use <application>vgdisplay</application> to find out the free physical "
"extents - Free PE / size (the size you can allocate). We will assume a free "
"size of 511 PE (equivalent to 2GB with a PE size of 4MB) and we will use the "
"whole free space available. Use your own PE and/or free space."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1110(para)
msgid ""
"The Logical Volume (LV) can now be extended by different methods, we will "
"only see how to use the PE to extend the LV:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1115(command)
msgid "sudo lvextend /dev/vg01/srv -l +511"
msgstr "sudo lvextend /dev/vg01/srv -l +511"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1118(para)
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>-l</emphasis> option allows the LV to be extended using PE. "
"The <emphasis>-L</emphasis> option allows the LV to be extended using Meg, "
"Gig, Tera, etc bytes."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1126(para)
msgid ""
"Even though you are supposed to be able to <emphasis>expand</emphasis> an "
"ext3 or ext4 filesystem without unmounting it first, it may be a good "
"pratice to unmount it anyway and check the filesystem, so that you don't "
"mess up the day you want to reduce a logical volume (in that case unmounting "
"first is compulsory)."
msgstr ""
"Même si vous êtes censé être en mesure d' <emphasis>agrandir</emphasis> un "
"système de fichiers ext3 ou ext4 sans démontage préalable, c'est une bonne "
"pratique de néanmoins le démonter et de vérifier le système de fichiers, "
"afin de ne pas avoir de mauvais réflexes le jour où vous souhaiterez réduire "
"un volume logique (dans ce cas, un démontage préalable est obligatoire)."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1132(para)
msgid ""
"The following commands are for an <emphasis>EXT3</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>EXT4</emphasis> filesystem. If you are using another filesystem "
"there may be other utilities available."
msgstr ""
"Les commandes suivantes sont pour un système de fichiers "
"<emphasis>EXT3</emphasis> ou <emphasis>EXT4</emphasis>. Si vous utilisez un "
"autre système de fichiers, il peut exister d'autres utilitaires disponibles."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1139(command)
msgid "sudo e2fsck -f /dev/vg01/srv"
msgstr "sudo e2fsck -f /dev/vg01/srv"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1142(para)
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>-f</emphasis> option of <application>e2fsck</application> "
"forces checking even if the system seems clean."
msgstr ""
"L'option <emphasis>-f</emphasis> de <application>e2fsck</application> force "
"le contrôle, même si le système semble propre."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1149(para)
msgid "Finally, resize the filesystem:"
msgstr "Enfin, redimensionnez le système de fichiers :"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1154(command)
msgid "sudo resize2fs /dev/vg01/srv"
msgstr "sudo resize2fs /dev/vg01/srv"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1160(para)
msgid "Now mount the partition and check its size."
msgstr "Montez ensuite la partition et vérifiez sa taille."

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1165(command)
msgid "mount /dev/vg01/srv /srv &amp;&amp; df -h /srv"
msgstr "mount /dev/vg01/srv /srv &amp;&amp; df -h /srv"

#: serverguide/C/installation.xml:1177(para)
msgid ""
"See the <ulink "
"url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Installation#lvm\">Ubuntu Wiki LVM "
